cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC

This paper is about Neural Architecture Search (NAS) which is a subfield of computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) and Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) which are techniques used in artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE), respectively. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.NE are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of distributed computing (DC) to accelerate the search process, which makes cs.DC a possible category as well.
